    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Measurements for shell morphology, spire profiles and types of siphonal canals; AA: apical angle, MD: maxium diameter." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376254/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376256>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Fusoterebra terebrina (Bellardi & Michelotti, 1840). A1–A2. NHMW 1997z/0178/1787, Walbersdorf (Austria). B1–B2. NHMW 1997z/0178/1787, Walbersdorf (Austria). C1–C2. NHMW 1997z/0178/1787, Walbersdorf (Austria). D1–D2. NHMW 1846/0037/0121, Baden (Austria), lectotype of Terebra fusiformis Hörnes 1852.F. NHMW 1866/0001/1055, Forchtenau (Austria), holotype of Terebra bigranulata Hoernes & Auinger, 1880. E1–E2. NHMW 2023/0292/0001, Baden Sooss (Austria)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376256/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376260>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Protoconchs of Paratethyan Terebridae. A. Fusoterebra terebrina (Bellardi & Michelotti, 1840), NHMW 2023/0294/0001, Baden (Austria). B. Hastula duboisiana (d’Orbigny, 1852), NHMW 2023/0295/0001, Bad Vöslau (Austria). C. Hastula lapugyensis (Hoernes & Auinger, 1880), NHMW 2023/0296/0001, Lăpugiu de Sus (Romania). D. Hastula translata (Sacco, 1891), holotype, NHMW 2023/0301/0001, Pöls (Austria). E. Strioterebrum borianum (Švagrovský, 1982), NHMW 2023/0298/0003, Gainfarn (Austria). F. Hastulopsis excostellata (Sacco, 1891), NHMW 2023/0295/0005, Bad Vöslau (Austria)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376260/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376262>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Hastula duboisiana (d’Orbigny, 1852). A1–A2. Lectotype, NHMW 1864/0001/0136, Bad Vöslau (Austria). B1–B2. Paralectotype, NHMW 1864/0001/0136a, Bad Vöslau (Austria). C1–C2. NHMW 1854/0035/0117, Lăpugiu de Sus (Romania). D1–D2. NHMW 1968/0001/0417, Lăpugiu de Sus (Romania). E1–E2. NHMW 1870/0033/0051, Lăpugiu de Sus (Romania). F. NHMW 2018/0248/0253, CoŞteiu de Sus (Romania). G1–G2. NHMW 2023/0293/0002, Baden (Austria)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376262/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376264>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Hastula sublaevigata (Grateloup, 1845). A1–A2. syntype of Hastula subcinerea (d’Orbigny, 1852), MNHN. F.B27640, Burdigalian (Early Miocene), region of Bordeaux (France)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376264/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

